## SIGNAL Terminal Frontend Code Analysis

I've thoroughly examined the terminal frontend codebase. Here's the complete structure:

### 1. **News Item Rendering & Table Structure**

**File:** `/home/haotiant/Projects/Personal/InstantNews/frontend/src/terminal-app.js` (lines 287-329)

**Table Structure (HTML):** 5-column table with:
- Time (70px width, monospace)
- Sentiment (80px width)
- Source (120px width)
- Headline (flexible)
- Summary (25% width, min 120px)

**Row Building Process:**
- Each news item rendered as `<tr class="${rowClass}" data-id="${item.id}">` (line 315)
- Rows use `news-row-new` animation class when item is newly fetched (line 310)
- Each row contains 5 `<td>` cells populated from item object

**Data Structure for Each Item:**
```javascript
item = {
  id: string,                    // Unique identifier
  title: string,                 // Headline
  summary: string,               // Truncated to 120 chars in display
  link: string,                  // External URL (opens in new tab)
  source: string,                // Feed source name
  published: ISO8601 string,    // Publication timestamp
  fetched_at: ISO8601 string,   // When article was fetched
  sentiment_label: "bullish" | "bearish" | "neutral", // Sentiment classification
  duplicate: boolean,            // Duplicate detection flag
}
```

**Display Processing:**
- **Time:** `formatTime(item.published)` → "HH:MM:SS" format (line 311)
- **Sentiment:** Badge with color (green/red/yellow) and sentiment-dot indicator (line 317)
- **Source:** Tag-style display with background color (line 318)
- **Headline:** Link with optional `badge-new` and `badge-dup` badges (line 320)
- **Summary:** Escaped HTML, truncated to 120 chars with ellipsis (line 322)

---

### 2. **Tier Checking Implementation**

**File:** `/home/haotiant/Projects/Personal/InstantNews/frontend/src/terminal-app.js` (lines 799-829)

**Tier Fetch Function:**
```javascript
async function fetchTier() {
  const res = await SignalAuth.fetch(`${API}/auth/tier`);
  const data = await res.json();
  const rawTier = data.tier || "free";
  const tier = rawTier === "plus" ? "pro" : rawTier;  // Normalize "plus" → "pro"

  // Update UI badge
  const badge = $("#tier-badge");
  badge.textContent = tier.toUpperCase();
  badge.className = "tier-badge" + (tier !== "free" ? " " + tier : "");

  // Client-side access gate (defense in depth)
  const features = data.features || {};
  if (features.terminal_access === false || tier === "free") {
    showUpgradeGate();  // Blocks free users
  } else {
    hideUpgradeGate();  // Allows pro users
  }
}
```

**Tiers Supported:**
- `"free"` - No terminal access (gated with overlay)
- `"pro"` / `"plus"` - Full terminal access

**API Response Format:**
```javascript
{
  tier: "free" | "pro" | "plus",
  features: {
    terminal_access: boolean
  }
}
```

**Tier Badge Location:** Header top-right next to user avatar (HTML line 120)

---

### 3. **Auth System (SignalAuth)**

**File:** `/home/haotiant/Projects/Personal/InstantNews/frontend/src/auth.js` (859 lines)

**Public API Methods:**
```javascript
SignalAuth.getUser()          // Returns {uid, email, displayName, photoURL}
SignalAuth.isSignedIn()       // Boolean
SignalAuth.fetch(url, opts)   // Auto-attaches Bearer token to requests
SignalAuth.getToken()         // Returns _appToken or _idToken
SignalAuth.signOut()          // Clears auth state
```

**Token Handling:**
- **App Token** (`_appToken`): JWT from backend email/password auth, stored in localStorage as `signal_app_token`
- **ID Token** (`_idToken`): Firebase OAuth token from Google sign-in
- Both tokens automatically added via `SignalAuth.fetch()` in Authorization header (line 377-380)

**Auth Change Listener:**
```javascript
SignalAuth.onAuthChange((user) => {
  // Called when user logs in/out
  // user is null when logged out
});
```

**Region Detection:** Automatic (global vs China), cached in localStorage

---

### 4. **HTML Template Structure**

**File:** `/home/haotiant/Projects/Personal/InstantNews/frontend/terminal.html`

**Key Sections:**
1. **Header** (lines 26-133):
   - Logo and clock
   - Connection status indicator
   - Stats (items count, feeds, avg sentiment)
   - API Docs button
   - Sound toggle
   - Refresh button
   - Sign in / User menu (auth dependent)

2. **Sidebar** (lines 143-243):
   - Search input (F shortcut)
   - Date range filter
   - Duplicate hide toggle
   - Sentiment filter buttons (1-4 keyboard shortcuts)
   - Source checkboxes
   - Refresh interval selector
   - Keyboard shortcuts hint

3. **Main Content** (lines 248-263):
   - `<table class="news-table">` with `<tbody id="news-body">` populated by JS

4. **Status Bar** (lines 268-285):
   - Last refresh time
   - Items per second rate
   - Site links and API endpoint

5. **API Docs Modal** (lines 288-376):
   - Modal overlay with overlay ID `#modal-overlay`
   - Toggles with `toggleModal(open)` function
   - Shows GET /news, /sources, /stats, POST /refresh endpoints

6. **Auth Gate Overlay** (lines 378-407):
   - Full-screen overlay for Free-tier users blocking terminal
   - Created dynamically by `showUpgradeGate()` with ID `#upgrade-gate`

---

### 5. **CSS Variables & Dark Terminal Theme**

**File:** `/home/haotiant/Projects/Personal/InstantNews/frontend/src/styles/terminal.css`

**Design Tokens (lines 7-68):**
```css
/* Backgrounds */
--bg-primary: #0d1117;        /* Main background */
--bg-surface: #161b22;         /* Panel backgrounds */
--bg-surface-2: #1c2128;       /* Secondary panels */
